#   GIT-007: JABC pack-log binding ‚Äî pure marshalling over the dog/git core, delete the duplicated logic

##  Input

### Context

Child of [[GIT-001]]; depends on [[GIT-002]]/[[GIT-004]]. `js/pack.hpp` is a third copy of pack-log logic: `JABCPackFeedOfs` (`:23`) is a hand-rolled replica of keeper's `pack_feed_ofs`, `JABCpackFeed` (`:58`) re-implements the raw-vs-OFS_DELTA decision (inflate base, `DELTEncode`, size compare, emit header+ofs varint+deflate), and `JABCpackNext` (`:120`) re-inflates to learn a record's compressed length. Once [[GIT-002]] lands the writer and [[GIT-004]] the resolver in dog/git, the binding must hold NO pack-log logic ‚Äî it only marshals JS typed arrays into `u8s` and calls the dog/git functions. See [PackLog], [INDEX], [CLAUDE].

 -  Triple duplication: the OFS varint encoder, the feed delta-decision, and the record-end scan exist once in keeper, once in dog/git (post GIT-002/004), and once in the binding ‚Äî a format tweak must be written three times and they can drift. `JABCpackFeed`'s delta-or-raw block is a line-for-line copy of `KEEPPackFeed`'s inner emit (`keeper/KEEP.c:1709-1766`); the landed `PACKu8sFeedOfs` dedup was necessary but insufficient ‚Äî the surrounding inflate-base / `DELTEncode` / size-compare / emit-hdr+deflate sequence is still duplicated.
 -  Format logic in a leaf binding violates the JABC charter ([INDEX]): the native layer is meant to be leaf-only (syscalls + typed-array fills); pack-log encoding is not a leaf concern.
 -  `malloc` scratch: `JABCpackFeed`/`JABCpackNext` `malloc` base + delta buffers, against [CLAUDE] ¬ß5 (resource allocation at the top of the call chain; BASS carve for scratch).
 -  Local defects to clear in the rewrite (not just relocate): `binto` and `basec` re-derive the identical base range (`js/pack.hpp:77`/`:83`); and `PACKu8sFeedObjHdr`'s return is ignored in the OFS arm (`:90`) but checked in the raw arm (`:102`), so a near-full buffer can emit a partial OFS header, fail the deflate, and let the raw fallback write a SECOND header over the advanced head ‚Äî latent double-header corruption, masked today only because JS sizes the buffer to fit.

### Goals
 -  Reduce `js/pack.hpp` to pure marshalling over the dog/git pack-log core, holding zero delta/encode/inflate decisions.
 -  Delete the duplicated pack-log logic (`JABCPackFeedOfs`, the inline feed delta-decision, the re-inflate record-end scan) once [[GIT-002]]/[[GIT-004]] land.
 -  Clear the local defects in the rewrite: the `binto`/`basec` base-range dup and the latent double-header corruption from the ignored OFS-arm return.

### Constraints
 -  Marshalling only: each `js/pack.hpp` entry resolves a typed array to a `u8s` (the one boundary touch, `JABCBytesOf`) and calls a dog/git PACK function; zero delta/encode/inflate decisions in the binding.
 -  Scratch is caller-provided: the dog/git feed/resolve functions take a caller buffer (or BASS carve), so the binding passes a JS-owned `Buf`/`Uint8Array`; no `malloc` in the binding.
 -  The JS-side sha‚Üí(offset) index STAYS in JS: it is the entry-boundary policy (the binding's analog of keeper's refs/LSM), not format logic ‚Äî keep building it over the `hit`/`hash` bindings (the "wh128 layer above" noted in `pack.hpp`).
 -  Delete `JABCPackFeedOfs` outright ‚Äî it is replaced by `PACKu8sFeedOfs` (GIT-002); the binding never open-codes a varint.

